cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new methodology for assessing and measuring the data distribution of a generative model using persistent homology. It also compares the performance of the proposed method with another type of generative model, Variational Auto-Encoders. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image reconstruction using auto-encoders. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a new methodology for improving the performance of generative models. The paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as auto-encoders are a type of neural network architecture. Finally, it involves statistical learning (cs.SI) as it proposes a new distance measure for comparing decoded samples of high quality in the context of credit card transactions.
